      "span_text": "Indeed, demonstrated that primary mammary epithelial cells collected from BALB/c mice and exposed in vitro to 3.0 Gy of 137 Cs γ-rays at 0.74 Gy/min. dose rate exhibited a marked increase in the frequency of radiation-induced genomic instability, whereas no such effect was observed in the same cells collected from C57BL/6 mice; in the latter animals frequency of the radiation-induced chromatid-type aberrations after the rapid clearance of initial aberrations remained at or near that detected in non-irradiated controls."
